Marsh & McLennan Companies, Inc (NYSE:MMC) Sees Unusual Trading Volume in Its Shares - Highlight Press

























































Highlight PressBreaking Tech News, Entertainment, Mortgages and More
Marsh & McLennan Companies, Inc (NYSE:MMC) Sees Unusual Trading Volume in Its Shares
July 25, 2017 By Clarence Martin Tweet        Advertisement





Trading volume for Marsh & McLennan Companies, Inc was 44K by the end of trading on Tuesday.  Overall, volume was down 97.56% under the stocks normal daily volume. 
 There has been some selling insider activity on Marsh & McLennan Companies, Inc (NYSE:MMC) recently.   Laurie Ledford, Sr VP sold $13,644,099 worth of shares at an average price of $74.03 on May 16th. The Sr VP now owns $390,770 of the stock per an SEC filing yesterday.
 The following firms have also recently changed their position in MMC.   As of quarter end Regentatlantic Capital LLC had sold  a total of 443 shares trimming its stake by 2.5%. The value of the total investment in Marsh & McLennan Companies, Inc increased from $1,316,000 to $1,354,000 a change of 2.9% since the last quarter. As of the end of the quarter Pggm Investments had disposed of 73,797 shares trimming its holdings by 16.4%. The value of the company’s investment in Marsh & McLennan Companies, Inc went from $33,237,000 to $29,315,000 decreasing 11.8% for the reporting period.
 Osborne Partners Capital Management, LLC expanded its holdings by buying 1,590 shares an increase of 1.6% from 03/31/2017 to 06/30/2017. Osborne Partners Capital Management, LLC owns 103,419 shares worth $8,063,000. The value of the position overall is up by 7.2%. APG Asset Management N.V. augmented its position by buying 10,100 shares an increase of 0.4%. APG Asset Management N.V. now holds 2,721,992 shares valued at $212,206,000. The total value of its holdings increased 5.9%.
  On July 13 Citigroup left the company rating at “Buy” but raised the price target  to $90.00 from $76.00. On November 7 the stock rating was upgraded from “” to “Buy” by Sandler O'Neill.
 On November 4, 2016 the stock rating was set at “Outperform” according to a BMO Capital report a boost from the previous “” rating. October 11 investment analysts at Citigroup held the stock rating at “Buy” but raised the price expectation from $64.00 to $76.00.





 On September 30 Barclays left the stock rating at “Overweight” and raised the price target  to $77.00 from $64.00. July 29 investment analysts at Deutsche Bank made no change to the stock rating of “Buy” and raised the price expectation from $61.00 to $71.00.
 In the market the company is trading up from yesterday’s close of $80.28.  Additionally Marsh & McLennan Companies, Inc recently declared a dividend for shareholders payable on Tuesday August 15th, 2017.  The dividend will be $0.375 per share for the quarter which is $1.50 annualized.  This dividend represents a yeild of $1.87 which is the dividend as a percentage of the current share price.  The ex-dividend date has been established as Friday the 7th of July 2017. 
 Shares of the company are trading at $80.60 just a bit higher than the 50 day moving average of $78.60 and which is marginally over the 200 day moving average of $74.19.  The 50 day moving average was up $2.09 or +2.67% whereas the 200 day average was up by +8.76%. 
 Marsh & McLennan Companies, Inc currently has a P/E ratio of 22.67 and market cap is 41.49B.  In the latest earnings report the EPS was $3.56 and is expected to be $3.82 for the current year with 514,159,000 shares now outstanding.  Analysts expect next quarter’s EPS to be $0.79 with next year’s EPS anticipated to be $4.20. 
 Marsh & McLennan Companies, Inc., launched on March 17, 1969, is a professional services firm offering clients advice and solutions in risk, strategy and people. The Company is the parent company of various risk advisors and specialty consultants, including Marsh, the insurance broker, intermediary and risk advisor; Guy Carpenter, the risk and reinsurance specialist; Mercer, the provider of human resource (HR) and investment related financial advice and services, and Oliver Wyman Group, the management, economic and brand consultancy. The Company conducts business through two segments: Risk and Insurance Services, which includes risk management activities (risk advice, risk transfer and risk control and mitigation solutions), as well as insurance and reinsurance broking and services, and Consulting includes health, retirement, talent and investments consulting services and products, and specialized management, economic and brand consulting services..






