Marsh & McLennan Companies Announces Executive Changes
Jul 6 17
Marsh & McLennan Companies announced that it has appointed John Doyle as CEO, succeeding Peter Zaffino, who is leaving for AIG. Doyle was named president of Marsh in April of 2016. Prior to joining the company, he was head of AIG's commercial insurance business worldwide.


Marsh Announces Executive Changes
Jun 9 17
Marsh announced senior leadership positions within its Aircraft Finance Insurance Consortium (AFIC). Leading aircraft finance specialist Robert Morin joins AFIC as Transaction and Business Development Leader, and Gabriel Okolski is appointed as Credit and Financial Analyst. Both are based in Washington, D.C. Morin joins Marsh from the Export-Import Bank of the United States (EXIM Bank), where he was Senior Vice President of Business and Product Development, a position he held since 2014. Okolski also joins Marsh from EXIM Bank, where he was a Senior Transportation Loan Officer responsible for more than $3 billion in large commercial aircraft and helicopter financing for airlines, aircraft leasing companies, and other corporate entities.


Marsh & McLennan Companies, Inc. Announces Quarterly Cash Dividend, Payable on August 15, 2017
May 18 17
Marsh & McLennan Companies, Inc. announced that the Board of Directors increased the quarterly cash dividend from $0.34 to $0.375 per share on outstanding common stock. The dividend is payable on August 15, 2017 to stockholders of record on July 11, 2017.


